# Import Organization

## Import Order
1. External dependencies (React, Next.js, third-party)
2. Internal imports using `@/` alias
3. Type imports (when separate from value imports)
4. Relative imports (avoid when possible)

```typescript
// ✅ Correct
'use client'

import { useState } from 'react'
import Link from 'next/link'
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'
import { content } from '@/lib/content'
import { SECTIONS } from '@/constants'
import type { SectionId } from '@/constants'
```

## Path Aliases
- Always use `@/` alias for internal imports
- Never use relative paths like `../../` when `@/` is available

```typescript
// ✅ Correct
import { content } from '@/lib/content'
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'
import { useNavigation } from '@/hooks/useNavigation'

// ❌ Incorrect
import { content } from '../../lib/content'
import { Button } from '../ui/button'
```

## Import Grouping
- Group imports by category with blank lines between groups
- Sort imports alphabetically within groups
